  "prompt": "I am an average student preparing for the IIT-JEE. Which test series is the best for me for free?",
  "response": "There are several test series options available for IIT-JEE preparation that are free or offer free trials. Here are some well-regarded options:\n\n1. **National Testing Agency (NTA) Mock Tests**:\n   - The official NTA website provides free mock tests for JEE Main. These mock tests simulate the actual exam scenario and are quite helpful for understanding the exam pattern and improving time management.\n\n2. **Edurev**:\n   - Edurev offers free test series for IIT-JEE, including topic-wise and full-length mock tests. It\u2019s a platform with a vast collection of study materials and tests.\n\n3. **Career 360**:\n   - Career 360 provides free test preparation resources for IIT-JEE, including mock tests and previous years' papers.\n\n4. **Embibe**:\n   - Embibe offers free test series along with detailed performance analysis. It is a valuable resource for personalized feedback and improvement.\n\n5. **Khan Academy**:\n   - Khan Academy provides free practice problems and instructional videos, which can be very helpful for IIT-JEE preparation.\n\n6. **Unacademy**:\n   - Unacademy offers special classes and test series for IIT-JEE which can be accessed for free. They have various educators providing valuable insights for exam preparation.\n\n7. **Gradeup**:\n   - Gradeup provides free mock tests and previous years' papers which are helpful for IIT-JEE aspirants.\n\n8. **MyPAT**:\n   - MyPAT occasionally offers free test series and has a free trial period. They provide good quality mock tests and analysis.\n\nRemember to consistently take these tests, analyze your performance, and work on your weak areas. Combining these free test series with disciplined self-study will enhance your preparation effectively.",
